In this article, President Barack Obama declares September 18-24, 2016, as Prescription Opioid and Heroin Epidemic Awareness Week. The article highlights the alarming statistics surrounding drug overdoses, with more Americans dying from drug overdoses than traffic accidents, and three out of five of these deaths involving opioids. The number of overdose deaths involving opioids has nearly quadrupled since 1999. The article emphasizes the importance of raising awareness and addressing the misconceptions and stigmas surrounding opioid use disorder and substance use disorder. The Federal Government is working to expand treatment and prevention activities, and to get more people into treatment instead of jail. President Obama calls on Congress to provide $1.1 billion to expand access to treatment services for opioid use disorder. The article concludes by urging everyone to observe the Prescription Opioid and Heroin Epidemic Awareness Week and support programs that raise awareness about the issue.